# Offerloop UI Redesign - Complete Implementation Guide

## Mission
Transform Offerloop from generic SaaS template to a clean, intelligent, Linear-meets-Arc aesthetic. Monochrome foundation with intentional purple gradient accents. No cards, no fluff, maximum clarity.

---

## Design System Reference

### Typography
- **Font**: Satoshi (replace ALL instances of current fonts)
- **Import**: `@import url('https://api.fontshare.com/v2/css?f[]=satoshi@400,500,700&display=swap');`
- **Mono font**: SF Mono, Monaco, or Cascadia Code for numbers/data

### Colors - Monochrome + Purple
```css
/* Light Mode */
--bg-primary: #FFFFFF;
--bg-secondary: #FAFAFA;
--bg-tertiary: #F5F5F5;

--text-primary: #000000;
--text-secondary: #666666;
--text-tertiary: #999999;

--border-light: #E5E5E5;
--border-medium: #D4D4D4;
--border-strong: #A3A3A3;

/* Purple Gradient (INTENTIONAL USE ONLY) */
--accent-from: #8B5CF6;
--accent-to: #D946EF;
--accent-solid: #A855F7;
--accent-soft: #F3E8FF;

/* Dark Mode */
--bg-primary-dark: #000000;
--bg-secondary-dark: #0A0A0A;
--bg-tertiary-dark: #141414;

--text-primary-dark: #FFFFFF;
--text-secondary-dark: #A3A3A3;
--text-tertiary-dark: #666666;

--border-light-dark: #1F1F1F;
--border-medium-dark: #2E2E2E;
--border-strong-dark: #3D3D3D;

--accent-soft-dark: #2E1065;
```

**Gradient Usage Rules (ONLY USE FOR):**
- Logo and branding elements
- Primary CTA buttons
- Credit counter badge
- Success celebration states
- **NEVER use on**: backgrounds, cards, containers, decorative elements

